    "/#X-Amz-Target=TrentService.DeleteAlias": {
      "post": {
        "operationId": "DeleteAlias",
        "description": "<p>Deletes the specified alias. You cannot perform this operation on an alias in a different AWS account. </p> <p>Because an alias is not a property of a CMK, you can delete and change the aliases of a CMK without affecting the CMK. Also, aliases do not appear in the response from the <a>DescribeKey</a> operation. To get the aliases of all CMKs, use the <a>ListAliases</a> operation. </p> <p>Each CMK can have multiple aliases. To change the alias of a CMK, use <a>DeleteAlias</a> to delete the current alias and <a>CreateAlias</a> to create a new alias. To associate an existing alias with a different customer master key (CMK), call <a>UpdateAlias</a>.</p>",
